    <section class="band band-alt" id="intellij-built-in-dependency-tools">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-number">IntelliJ</span>
          <h2>How is AtlasArc different from IntelliJ's built-in dependency tools?</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="section-intro">IntelliJ IDEA already includes useful tools for dependency analysis, module diagrams, cyclic dependency checks, and Dependency Structure Matrix exploration. AtlasArc doesn't replace those general-purpose IDE features. It builds on the same local-first workflow and adds the architecture layer on top: every lens reads one shared model, so cycle states, boundaries, hotspots, governance, and reports stay in sync as you move between them.</p>

        <div class="feature-table-wrap">
          <table class="feature-table compare-intellij-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Area</th>
                <th>IntelliJ built-in dependency tools</th>
                <th>AtlasArc contrast</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Best fit</strong></td>
                <td>Inspect dependencies, module relationships, cyclic dependencies, usage paths, and package/class relationships inside the IDE.</td>
                <td>Run a repeatable architecture review: <a href="/product/features#explore-structure">map</a>, <a href="/product/features#diagnose-structural-problems">diagnose</a>, <a href="/product/features#expose-risky-code">expose</a>, <a href="/product/features#prioritize-refactoring-work">prioritize</a>, <a href="/product/features#govern-exceptions">govern</a>, and <a href="/product/features#review-and-report">report</a>.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Graph support</strong></td>
                <td>Module dependency diagrams, package/class dependency views, and Gradle/Maven dependency diagrams in relevant contexts.</td>
                <td><a href="/lenses/topology-graph">Interactive topology graph</a> with package/source-folder expansion and a Topology-only contained class/file internals layer.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Matrix support</strong></td>
                <td>DSM plugin for matrix-style dependency exploration; requires an Ultimate subscription.</td>
                <td><a href="/lenses/package-matrix">Dedicated Dependency Matrix</a> over AtlasArc's shared architecture model, aligned with other lenses.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Cycle support</strong></td>
                <td>Cyclic dependency analysis and visual highlighting of circular dependencies.</td>
                <td><a href="/metrics/cyclic-dependencies">Architecture-specific cycle states</a>: architectural, nested, aggregation, and governed cycles, separating genuine cycles from loops caused by collapsed folders and decisions the team already recorded.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Navigation</strong></td>
                <td>Strong IDE-native navigation: jump to source, find usages, inspect dependencies.</td>
                <td>IDE-local narrowing around <a href="/product/features#explore-structure">subject pinning</a>, Neighbourhood, Boundary Graph, Boundary Matrix, breadcrumb, and Status Cluster.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
