              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>TypeScript relevance</strong></td>
                <td>Not the comparison point for the Java/IDE dependency-analysis docs reviewed.</td>
                <td><a href="/languages/typescript">TypeScript architecture exploration</a> via user-generated dependency-cruiser artifacts.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-faq" id="faq-intellij-dependency-analyzer">
          <h3>How is AtlasArc different from IntelliJ IDEA's built-in dependency analyzer?</h3>
          <p>IntelliJ IDEA's tools are great for a quick local question: who depends on this, where's the cycle, what's in this module. AtlasArc is for the standing architecture review around those answers. One shared model feeds every lens, cycles carry architectural states instead of a single flag, you can pin a subject and read its boundary, and accepted exceptions stay in source where the team reviews them and CI enforces them.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
